#: index.docbook:57
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Introduction"

#: index.docbook:59
msgid ""
"&ktalkd; is an enhanced <command>talk</command>"
" daemon - a program to handle incoming <command>talk</command> requests, "
"announce them and allow you to respond to it using a <command>talk</command>"
" client."
msgstr ""
"&ktalkd; est un démon de discussion amélioré - le programme qui traite "
"les demandes de discussion entrantes, les annonce et vous permet d'y "
"répondre à l'aide d'un client de discussion."

#: index.docbook:65
msgid ""
"Note that &ktalkd; is designed to run on a single-user workstation, and "
"shouldn't be run on a multi-user machine: since it reads users' "
"configuration files, users can get the <command>talk</command>"
" daemon to run any command, which is particularly dangerous. Do not use "
"ktalkd if you create accounts on your machine, to people you don't fully "
"trust."
msgstr ""

#: index.docbook:75
msgid ""
"In this document, if somebody wants to talk to you, you are designated as "
"the <quote>callee</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Dans ces pages, vous êtes désigné comme l' <quote>appelé</quote> "
"lorsqu'une personne désire vous parler."

#: index.docbook:80
msgid "&ktalkd; has the following features :"
msgstr "&ktalkd; a les caractéristiques suivantes&nbsp;:"

#: index.docbook:82
msgid "Answering machine"
msgstr "Répondeur téléphonique"

#: index.docbook:82
msgid ""
"If the callee isn't logged on, or doesn't answer after the second "
"announcement, an answering machine is launched, takes the message, and mails "
"it to the callee."
msgstr ""
"Si l'appelé n'est pas connecté ('login'), ou ne répond pas après le "
"second avis, un répondeur automatique est lancé, prend le message, et "
"l'envoie sous forme de courrier électronique à l'appelé."

#: index.docbook:82
msgid "Sound"
msgstr "Son"

#: index.docbook:82
msgid "If desired, a sound is played with the announcement."
msgstr "Si c'est souhaité, un son est joué en même temps que l'avis est affiché."

#: index.docbook:82
msgid "X Announce"
msgstr "Avis X"

#: index.docbook:82
msgid ""
"If compiled with &kde; installed, &ktalkd; will use "
"<literal>ktalkdlg</literal>, a &kde; dialog, for announcement. If "
"<application>ktalk</application> is running, it will be asked to make the "
"announcement itself. (New since 0.8.8)."
msgstr ""
"Si &ktalkd; est compilé alors que &kde; est installé, ktalkd utilisera "
"<literal>ktalkdlg</literal>, une boîte de dialogue &kde;, pour afficher "
"l'avis. Si <application>ktalk</application> fonctionne, c'est à lui qu'on "
"demandera de faire l'annonce. (Nouveau depuis la version 0.8.8)."

#: index.docbook:82
msgid "Multiple displays annoucement"
msgstr "Avis multi-écrans"

#: index.docbook:82
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you are logged remotely (&eg; with an "
"<userinput><command>export</command> "
"<envar>DISPLAY</envar>=<replaceable>...</replaceable></userinput> command), "
"the X announcement will be made on this display too. Answer on the one you "
"want! If you're also logged in a text terminal, and if you're "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> using xterms (internal restriction), then you'll "
"see a text announcement too, in case you're using the text terminal at the "
"time of the announcement."
msgstr ""
"Si vous êtes connecté à distance (&pex; via une commande "
"<userinput><command>export</command> "
"<envar>DISPLAY</envar>=<replaceable>...</replaceable></userinput>), l'avisX "
"sera également fait sur cet écran. Répondez sur celui que vous "
"voulez&nbsp;! Si vous êtes également connecté sur un terminal de texte, "
"et si vous n'utilisez PAS xterm (restriction interne), alors vous verrez "
